            <div type="column">
               
                    <head type="main">TO WRITERS.</head>
                
                    <p>Be original. Don't filch whole sentences from other writers, without honest quotation marks. Don't treat us to Dickens and water&#8212;or Thackeray and water&#8212;or Bronte and water&#8212;or any other writer and water. Be yourself, or be nothing. (I <hi rend="italic">have</hi> known the terms synonymous!) Always remember, that in this reading age and community, <hi rend="italic">an imitation is sure to be seen through</hi>; and that in attempting servilely to copy the style of another, you not only fail of gaining his style, but you lose every chance of individuality for your own. If you have nothing to say, don't say it; if you have, for patience' sake, use your own words to do it in, though they may be rough as a nutmeg-grater. Second-hand literary goods are a drug in the market. </p>
                
                    <byline>FANNY FERN.</byline>                
               
            </div>
            
        </body>
        
